node.contents: Why encrypt only the last chunk of data? Btw. it will be almost always less than 64kB, for example if your file is 70kB, it'll be likely only about 5kB. It is also impossible to know where the encrypted portion starts given the contract for `read` which allows that less than the requested number of bytes is returned.

node.contents: Your code doesn't encrypt the last 64KB. It encrypts the last chunk, whatever its size, resulting from all the prior reads. If you want the last 64KB, God knows why, you have to seek() or skip() to the appropriate value, that is to say the file length minus 64KB.
